## 8. How to Run

```bash
# Backend
cd darkguard/backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
python3 manage.py migrate
python3 manage.py runserver           # http://localhost:8000

# Tests (111 tests)
python3 -m pytest -v

# Extension
cd darkguard/extension
npm install
npx tsc --noEmit                      # type-check
npx vite build                        # build to dist/

# Load Extension
# Chrome → Extensions → Load Unpacked → select extension/dist/
```

---

## 9. How to Add a New Analyzer

Follow this exact pattern:

```
new_analyzer/
├── __init__.py          # AnalyzerRegistry.register(NewAnalyzerService())
├── interfaces.py        # Typed payload dataclass
├── service.py           # class NewAnalyzerService(BaseAnalyzer)
└── tests/
    ├── __init__.py
    └── test_new_analyzer.py
```

**`__init__.py`**:
```python
from core.registry import AnalyzerRegistry
from new_analyzer.service import NewAnalyzerService
AnalyzerRegistry.register(NewAnalyzerService())
```

**`service.py`** must implement:
```python
class NewAnalyzerService(BaseAnalyzer):
    @property
    def name(self) -> str: return "new_analyzer"

    @property
    def required_payload_keys(self) -> list[str]: return ["text_content"]

    async def analyze(self, payload: dict[str, object]) -> list[Detection]: ...
```

Then add `"new_analyzer"` to `INSTALLED_APPS` in `settings.py` and add `"new_analyzer/tests"` to `testpaths` in `pyproject.toml`.

